alking%20business.%20I%20spent%20%242%2C000%20on%20the%20event%20and%20another%20%243%2C000%20on%20flights%2C%20hotels%2C%20and%20expenses.%20It%20was%20a%20big%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20digital%20nomad%2C%20I'd%20been%20surrounded%20by%20encouraging%20American%20friends%20and%20founders%20for%20years.%20But%20when%20I%20returned%20to%20London%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20shift.%20If%20I%20talked%20about%20my%20business%20goals%2C%20people%20would%20smile%20politely%20and%20change%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20flew%20to%20Arizona%2C%20hoping%20to%20feel%20that%20American%20energy%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20weeks%20showed%20me%20why%20British%20founders%20often%20feel%20stuck%20and%20forever%20changed%20the%20way%20I%20view%20British%20business%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cd49654-ddce-44b6-9d2d-583882b00a92%5C%22%3EThe%20enthusiasm%20gap%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrits%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20tall-poppy%20syndrome.%20People%20are%20less%20open%20to%20talking%20about%20goals%20and%20encouraging%20ambition%20than%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20founder%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20build%20his%20net%20worth%20to%20%2410%20million%20the%20next%20decade.%20Nobody%20flinched.%20Instead%2C%20they%20asked%20questions%20about%20his%20plan%20and%20offered%20ideas.%20Back%20in%20London%20a%20week%20earlier%2C%20I'd%20heard%20a%20friend%20call%20a%20%C2%A3100%2C000%20salary%20%26quot%3Bunrealistic.%26quot%3B%20That's%20the%20UK%20mindset%20%E2%80%94%20we%20talk%20ourselves%20out%20of%20ambition%20before%20we%20even%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arizona%2C%20when%20someone%20shared%20a%20big%20goal%2C%20the%20Americans%20asked%20%26quot%3BHow%20will%20you%20get%20there%3F%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20sure%20that's%20possible%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20home%20in%20London%2C%20I'd%20keep%20quiet%20about%20my%20wins.%20When%20I%20do%20share%20goals%2C%20I%20find%20myself%20adding%20disclaimers%20to%20couch%20my%20ambition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arizona%2C%20I%20could%20talk%20openly%20about%20my%20successes%20without%20feeling%20as%20if%20I%20were%20bragging.%20When%20I%20shared%20concerns%2C%20people%20helped%20me%20see%20them%20as%20challenges%20to%20solve%2C%20not%20roadblocks%20to%20stop%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20energy%20was%20contagious.%20I%20felt%20calm%20about%20where%20I%20was%20and%20excited%20about%20where%20I%20could%20go.%20Instead%20of%20questioning%20whether%20things%20would%20work%20out%2C%20I%20started%20asking%20how%20much%20bigger%20they%20could%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20back%20in%20London%2C%20I%20notice%20how%20quickly%20our%20culture%20can%20pull%20you%20back%20into%20doubt.%20It's%20as%20if%20we're%20playing%20two%20different%20games%3A%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20we%20compete%20to%20spot%20problems.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20they%20compete%20to%20spot%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22258945ec-8cd0-4321-b590-ca189b6fc4a2%5C%22%3EEntrepreneurship%20as%20a%20viable%20career%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20young%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20start%20businesses%20in%20the%20US%20because%20it's%20deemed%20a%20legitimate%20career%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%2C%20I%20was%20pushed%20toward%20higher%20education%20and%20a%20steady%20job%20as%20a%20young%20person%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2017%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20spend%20%C2%A350%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20the%20average%20price%20of%20British%20university%20%E2%80%94%20on%20a%20degree%2C%20all%20to%20get%20a%20job%20I%20didn't%20want.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20you're%20expected%20to%20go%20to%20university%20or%20trade%20school.%20When%20I%20said%20no%20to%20both%20and%20spoke%20about%20starting%20a%20business%2C%20my%20teachers%20were%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20pushed%20me%20to%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafe%26quot%3B%20job%20like%20accountancy.%20The%20subtext%20was%20entrepreneurship%20wasn't%20a%20real%20career.%20It%20was%20a%20phase%20I'd%20grow%20out%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arizona%2C%20I%20met%20successful%20founders%20from%20every%20background%20imaginable.%20Some%20had%20fancy%20degrees%3B%20others%20never%20finished%20high%20school.%20But%20they%20all%20saw%20entrepreneurship%20as%20a%20natural%20path%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20being%20whether%20people%20in%20America%20or%20the%20UK%20go%20on%20to%20start%20businesses%20isn't%20about%20intelligence%20or%20education.%20The%20problem%20is%20how%20entrepreneurship%20is%20perceived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20mindset%20gap%20starts%20early.%20While%20American%20kids%20grow%20up%20hearing%20stories%20about%20startup%20founders%2C%20as%20a%20British%20student%20I%20was%20raised%20to%20pursue%20job%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226adcd3b7-8ce1-4542-87e7-486887b57425%5C%22%3ETaking%20risks%20is%20normal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20four%20failed%20attempts%20to%20build%20a%20business%20until%20I%20finally%20started%20seeing%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20getting%20things%20wrong%20meant%20judgment%20and%20criticism.%20I%20built%20up%20walls%20and%20was%20less%20open%20about%20my%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20first%20business%20ventures%20was%20becoming%20a%20personal%20trainer%20at%2019.%20My%20peers%20found%20my%20website%20and%20sent%20anonymous%20emails%20mocking%20me.%20I%20quit%20after%20a%20year%2C%20but%20my%20family%20could%20never%20understand%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20the%20fear%20of%20failure%20that%20was%20holding%20me%20back%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20fear%20and%20embarrassment%20of%20being%20judged%20by%20others%20for%20trying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20failure%20was%20proof%20I%20was%20building.%20Each%20startup%20taught%20me%20about%20business%2C%20systems%2C%20and%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20founder%20I%20met%20at%20the%20mastermind%20had%20at%20least%20one%20failure%20story.%20They%20didn't%20hide%20them%20because%20they%20saw%20failure%20as%20proof%20that%20you're%20in%20the%20game%20and%20are%20resilient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ff12b9c-4d96-4f1e-9890-b69d3e1a393e%5C%22%3EInfectious%20energy%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpending%20time%20with%20American%20entrepreneurs%20felt%20like%20meeting%20a%20cousin%20who%20was%20raised%20with%20more%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20guys%20in%20our%20group%20was%20training%20for%20an%20ultramarathon.%20He%20had%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20self-belief%20and%20conviction%20I've%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20persuaded%20us%20all%20to%20run%20a%20practice%20marathon%20with%20him.%20With%20no%20training%20and%20two%20hours%20of%20sleep%2C%20we%20set%20off%20at%203%20a.m.%20I%20had%20to%20drop%20out%20after%20the%2018th%20mile%2C%20but%20that's%20still%20farther%20than%20I've%20ever%20run%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20probably%20never%20have%20attempted%20it%20alone%2C%20but%20being%20around%20this%20level%20of%20confidence%20was%20infectious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%209%2C500%20millionaires%20left%20the%20UK%20in%202024%2C%20while%20the%20US%20gained%203%2C800.%20We%20spoke%20at%20the%20mastermind%20about%20why%20so%20many%20British%20founders%20are%20looking%20to%20exit%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20it's%20about%20the%20country's%20energy%20as%20much%20as%20tax%20changes.%20In%20those%20two%20weeks%20in%20the%20States%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20source%20of%20energy%20I'd%20never%20experienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20jet%20lag%20and%20constant%20socializing%2C%20I%20tapped%20into%20the%20enthusiasm%20of%20my%20peers%2C%20and%20it%20meant%20I%20had%20unlimited%20energy%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20home%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20not%20let%20the%20gray%20energy%20creep%20in.%20I%20have%20to%20be%20rigorous%20about%20self-care%20and%20my%20personal%20routines%20to%20maintain%20a%20steady%20baseline%20of%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20was%20in%20the%20States%2C%20the%20positivity%20and%20ambition%20of%20the%20people%20around%20me%20was%20like%20riding%20a%20wave%20that%20kept%20pulling%20me%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cf8d2893-9889-4da0-a166-20e94ae8546d%5C%22%3EThe%20UK's%20missing%20ingredient%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELondon%20has%20access%20to%20European%20talent%2C%20free%20healthcare%2C%20and%20reasonable%20taxes.%20We%20should%20be%20an%20innovation%20powerhouse%2C%20but%20something's%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20it's%20a%20cultural%20problem.%20We%20need%20to%20push%20ourselves%20to%20think%20bigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20a%20remote%20British%20village%2C%20I%20was%20taught%20to%20keep%20my%20head%20down%20and%20expectations%20low.%20%26quot%3BBe%20realistic%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20But%20ambition%20and%20optimism%20are%20good%20things%2C%20and%20we%20shouldn't%20hold%20back%20those%20who%20aspire%20for%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbritish-vs-american-entrepreneurship-difference-founder-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738664613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a0fe2e7bb3f854015b8632%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbritish-vs-american-entrepreneurship-difference-founder-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20British%20founder%20who%20traveled%20to%20the%20US%20for%20a%20business%20workshop%20shares%20his%20reflections%20on%20how%20differently%20the%20countries%20approach%20entrepreneurship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Tom%20Scourfield)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbritish-vs-american-entrepreneurship-difference-founder-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukrainian%20commander%20says%20North%20Korean%20soldiers%20charged%20his%20unit%20'like%20in%20