ps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-ceo-travis-kalanick-out-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresigned%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20sheer%20speed%20at%20which%20Uber's%20Chinese%20competitors%20copied%20the%20company's%20innovations%20was%20maddening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20way%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20that%20relentless%20approach%20eventually%20gave%20way%20to%20true%20innovation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20of%20ingenuity%20recently%20displayed%20by%20Chinese%20AI%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-r1-open-source-replicate-ai-west-china-hugging-face-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeepSeek%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20sent%20shockwaves%20through%20Silicon%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20I%20could%20express%20the%20frenetic%20intensity%20of%20copying%20that%20they%20would%20do%20on%20everything%20that%20we%20would%20roll%20out%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said%20on%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D8RkgkOqWs0s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAll-In%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20was%20so%20epically%20intense%20that%20I%20basically%20had%20a%20massive%20amount%20of%20respect%20for%20their%20ability%20to%20copy%20what%20we%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20the%20company%20was%20in%20a%20fierce%20battle%20for%20market%20share%20with%20Chinese%20rideshare%20rival%20Didi%20Chuxing%2C%20to%20which%20Uber%20would%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-didi-merged-with-uber%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esell%20its%20China%20operations%20in%202016.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20before%20DiDi%20absorbed%20Uber's%20China%20business%2C%20the%20pressure%20to%20outpace%20each%20other%20created%20a%20veritable%20arms%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20couldn't%20believe%20it.%20We%20would%20do%20real%20hard%20work%2C%20make%20it%2C%20we'd%20dial%20it%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20epic%20and%20it%20would%20be%20awesome%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe'd%20roll%20it%20out%2C%20and%20then%20like%20two%20weeks%20later%20%E2%80%94%20boom!%20They've%20got%20it.%20A%20week%20later%20%E2%80%94%20boom!%20They've%20got%20it.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20I%20used%20that%20to%20drive%20our%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-china-growth-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompetition%3C%2Fa%3E%20pushed%20Kalanick%20to%20recruit%20%26quot%3Bover%20400%20Chinese%20nationals%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20said%20created%20a%20sort%20of%20subculture%20within%20Uber's%20Silicon%20Valley%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20whole%20floor%20for%20the%20China%20growth%20team%20and%20it%20was%20primarily%20Chinese%20Nationals%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20billboards%20on%20the%20101%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20in%20Chinese%20%E2%80%94%20Uber%20billboards%20to%20join%20our%20team%20in%20Chinese%20%E2%80%94%20to%20serve%20the%20homeland%2C%20right%3F%20It%20was%20like%20an%20all-out%20war.%20It%20was%20really%20epic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Kalanick%20said%2C%20that%20furious%20pace%20of%20development%20%E2%80%94%20and%20getting%20used%20to%20working%20at%20that%20speed%20%E2%80%94%20gave%20way%20to%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20is%2C%20when%20you%20get%20really%2C%20really%20good%20at%20copying%2C%20and%20that%20time%20gets%20tighter%2C%20and%20tighter%2C%20and%20tighter%2C%20and%20tighter%2C%20and%20tighter%2C%20you%20eventually%20run%20out%20of%20things%20to%20copy%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20it%20flips%20to%20creativity%20and%20innovation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20Kalanick%20said%20that%20Chinese%20companies%20are%20now%20getting%20ahead%20of%20their%20American%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20as%20they%20exercise%20that%20muscle%2C%20it%20gets%20better%2C%20and%20better%2C%20and%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20know%20about%20the%20future%20of%20food%2C%20like%20online%20food%20delivery%2C%20you%20don't%20go%20to%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20you%20go%20to%20Shanghai.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20part%2C%20Chinese%20companies%20are%20well-positioned%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20circumstances%20that%20are%20unique%20to%20their%20country%2C%20Kalanick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20they're%20taking%20advantage%20of%20their%20economics%20on%20labor%20and%20things%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wouldn't%20exactly%20work%20that%20way%20here%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20innovation%20you%20will%20see%20coming%20out%20on%20Uber%20Eats%20or%20DoorDash%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20stuff%20that's%20coming%20out%20now%20%E2%80%94%20is%20stuff%20that%20existed%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20four%20years%20ago%20in%20China.%20Maybe%20longer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloudKitchens%20and%20DiDi%20Chuxing%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%20along%20the%20way%2C%20Chinese%20businesses%20went%20from%20lagging%20behind%20to%20setting%20the%20bar%20on%20innovative%20features%2C%20Kalanick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEventually%20you%20cross%20that%20threshold%20of%20copying%2C%20and%20you're%20innovating%2C%20and%20then%20you're%20leading%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalanick%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20we%20see%20that%20in%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20different%20places.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-founder-travis-kalanick-chinese-companies-compared-american-innovation-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738663382