known%20as%20molly%2C%20ecstasy%2C%20or%2C%20back%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20E%20%E2%80%94%20with%20people%20she%20trusted%20helped%20her%20experience%20music%20more%20deeply%20and%20connect%20with%20friends%20and%20loved%20ones%20on%20a%20whole%20new%20level.%20When%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20became%20parents%20in%202009%2C%20their%20drug%20use%20didn't%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESixteen%20years%20later%2C%20the%20couple%2C%20who%20are%20in%20their%20early%2050s%20and%20live%20in%20Toronto%2C%20remain%20embedded%20in%20what%20Gordon%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20drug-positive%20social%20culture.%26quot%3B%20Their%20friend%20group%2C%20which%20grew%20out%20of%20the%20electronic%20dance%20music%20fan%20community%2C%20is%20now%20made%20up%20of%20middle-age%2C%20established%20professionals%20with%20families.%20Many%20of%20them%20continue%20to%20attend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-parties-rave-nightlife-bars-clubs-trivia-online-quarantine-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparties%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20DJ%20events%20and%20use%20drugs%20on%20a%20fairly%20regular%20basis.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20Gordon%20said%2C%20drugs%20are%20part%20of%20the%20identity%20of%20her%20social%20life.%20Having%20this%20outlet%2C%20and%20the%20community%20that%20surrounds%20it%2C%20helps%20her%20be%20a%20more%20present%20parent%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20navigating%20drug%20use%20while%20raising%20kids%20isn't%20always%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody's%20a%20parent%20now%2C%20and%20everybody's%20coming%20to%20the%20parties%2C%20and%20sometimes%20people%20even%20rent%20an%20Airbnb%20for%20the%20kids%20to%20stay%20at%20and%20hire%20a%20babysitter%20who%20is%20capable%20of%20handling%20five%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20developing%20their%20lives%20around%20the%20drug-positive%20culture%2C%20but%20then%20it's%20like%20we%20have%20to%20cover%20our%20kids'%20ears%20when%20we%20go%20back%20home.%20It's%20kind%20of%20weird.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHers%20isn't%20the%20only%20friend%20group%20dancing%20between%20nightlife%20and%20parenting.%20A%202022%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faspe.hhs.gov%2Freports%2Fchildren-living-parents-using-substances%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20between%202015%20and%202019%2C%20more%20than%2021%20million%20US%20children%20lived%20with%20a%20parent%20who%20used%20illicit%20substances%2C%20which%20the%20report%20distinguished%20from%20parents%20who%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-am-the-child-of-addicted-to-drugs-parent-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubstance%20use%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20drug%20use%20has%20become%20more%20common%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20more%20adults%20are%20regularly%20partaking%20of%20both%20licit%20and%20illicit%20substances.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaldrugsurvey.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F2022WowReport_Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Drug%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonscientific%20survey%20that%20has%20grown%20into%20the%20world's%20largest%20annual%20survey%20of%20recreational%20drug%20use%20trends%2C%20found%20that%20self-reported%20use%20of%20drugs%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegal-cannabis-retail-sales-eclipse-chocolate-sales-in-us-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecannabis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20LSD%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bmagic%26quot%3B%20mushrooms%20was%20growing%20in%20the%20US.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20last%20year%20with%20available%20data%2C%20one-third%20of%2030-%20to%2039-year-olds%20and%20nearly%20one-quarter%20of%2040-%20to%2049-year-olds%20said%20they'd%20taken%20cocaine%20in%20the%20past%2012%20months.%20The%20same%20shares%20reported%20using%20MDMA%20in%20the%20past%20year.%20In%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9659323%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOf%2520266%2520responding%2520parents%252C%252034%2Cand%2520child%2520emotional%252Fbehavioral%2520problems.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20226%20American%20parents%2C%2013%25%20said%20they%20had%20used%20marijuana%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20age%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-ceos-founders-attended-burning-man%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBurning%20Man%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20unofficial%20wellness%20retreat%20for%20aging%20tech%20bros%2C%20none%20of%20this%20should%20come%20as%20breaking%20news.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychedelics-better-leaders-business-executives-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20gone%20on%20the%20record%20in%20recent%20years%20to%20sing%20the%20praises%20of%20mind-altering%20substances%20such%20as%20LSD%20and%20MDMA%2C%20with%20some%20even%20insisting%20that%20%26quot%3Btripping%26quot%3B%20had%20made%20them%20better%20at%20their%20jobs.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20researchers%20are%20discovering%20therapeutic%20benefits%20for%20psychedelic%20drugs%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fketamine-therapy-depression-treatment-addictive-drug-clinics-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eketamine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MDMA%2C%20and%20psilocybin%20(found%20in%20magic%20mushrooms).%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-cancer-risk-surgeon-general-report-smoking-cigarettes-obesity-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20risks%20of%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20become%20clearer%2C%20drugs%20are%20increasingly%20stepping%20in%20as%20the%20preferred%20indulgences%20for%20a%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychedelics-work-microdosing-lsd-psilocybin-ketamine-retreats-elon-musk-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20getting%20high%20has%20become%20a%20critical%20avenue%20for%20staying%20sane%20amid%20the%20demands%20of%20parenthood.%20And%20they're%20hoping%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20a%20better%20message%20than%20%26quot%3Bjust%20say%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20spring%2C%20Katie%2C%2037%2C%20rented%20a%20cabin%20with%20a%20friend%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%20and%20spent%20the%20weekend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrodosing-psilocybin-mushrooms-for-creativity-startups-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etripping%20on%20magic%20mushrooms%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20weekend%20to%20get%20loose%20with%20party%20drugs%20but%20a%20quiet%20getaway%20to%20embark%20on%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20trip%20together%20for%20more%20intellectual%20purposes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20While%20she%20was%20exploring%20the%20outer%20edges%20of%20her%20consciousness%2C%20her%208-year-old%20son%20was%20home%20with%20his%20dad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecreational%20drug%20use%20is%20a%20common%20feature%20of%20weekend%20get-togethers%20among%20Katie's%20New%20York%20City%20circle%20%E2%80%94%20a%20constellation%20of%20academics%2C%20creatives%2C%20and%20white-collar%20professionals%20who%20are%20mostly%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s.%20It's%20not%20unusual%20for%20her%20friends%20to%20pass%20around%20baggies%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-streets-underground-drug-abuse-culture-cocaine-adderall-zyn-mushrooms-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMDMA%20or%20cocaine%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fuel%20hours%20of%20dancing%20at%20a%20club%20or%20to%20consume%20mushrooms%20for%20a%20cozy%20night%20of%20soul-searching.%20Drugs%20are%20a%20conduit%20for%20shaking%20off%20the%20pressures%20of%20everyday%20life%2C%20for%20living%20in%20the%20moment%20with%20friends%2C%20and%20for%20Katie%20%E2%80%94%20getting%20back%20in%20touch%20with%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKatie%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20I%20keep%20her%20identity%20private%2C%20splits%20custody%20of%20her%20son%20with%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20an%20arrangement%20that%20has%20allowed%20her%20to%20reengage%20with%20nightlife.%20Before%20they%20separated%20nearly%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20late-night%20parties%20and%20drug%20use%20were%20off%20the%20table%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20it%20interfered%20with%20being%20a%20mother%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20because%20of%20the%20societal%20expectations%20modeled%20by%20her%20ex%20and%20the%20other%20parents%20around%20her.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20I%20am%20as%20a%20parent%20is%20maybe%20different%20%E2%80%94%20lighter%20and%20easier%20and%20freer%20%E2%80%94%20because%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20my%20life%20is%20limited%20in%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20parents%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20where%20it%20was%20typical%20to%20start%20families%20in%20your%20early%2020s%20while%20continuing%20to%20enjoy%20late%20weekend%20nights%20of%20well-lubricated%20merriment%2C%20with%20friends%20taking%20turns%20staying%20in%20to%20watch%20everyone's%20kids.%20But%20Katie%20has%20found%20that%20things%20are%20different%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20American%20culture%20doesn't%20prioritize%20having%20a%20robust%20social%20life%20while%20raising%20a%20family.%20For%20parents%20like%20her%2C%20there's%20a%20double%20taboo%3A%20the%20lingering%20stigmas%20surrounding%20recreational%20drug%20use%20combined%20with%20a%20widespread%20wariness%20of%20parents%2C%20especially%20moms%2C%20who%20manage%20to%20lead%20full%2C%20fun%20lives%20outside%20the%20confines%20of%20home.%20A%20mother%20who%20routinely%20nurses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnl-skit-captured-everything-uncomfortable-about-wine-mom-culture-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf%20a%20bottle%20of%20wine%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20her%20kitchen%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20day%20will%20likely%20be%20judged%20less%20harshly%20than%20one%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychedelics-key-long-happy-marriage-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etakes%20a%20psychedelic%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20friends%20on%20the%20occasional%20Saturday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsing%20drugs%20doesn't%20necessarily%20feel%20at%20odds%20with%20parenting%2C%26quot%3B%20Katie%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20feels%20complementary%20or%20helpful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20her%20son%20is%20a%20constant%20presence%20in%20her%20plans%2C%20during%20conversations%2C%20and%20at%20the%20dinners%20she%20hosts%20for%20friends%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20her%20inner%20circle%20is%20child-free.%20Other%20parents%20she's%20encountered%20don't%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20blueprint%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20community%20she%20has%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20isn't%20centered%20on%20the%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrug%20taboos%20get%20tricky%20to%20navigate%20when%20other%20people's%20children%20may%20be%20involved.%20%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20this%20thing%20you%20don't%20talk%20about%20because%20kids%20can't%20really%20be%20explaining%20to%20their%20friends%20on%20the%20schoolyard%20what%20Mommy%20and%20Daddy%20said%20last%20night%20about%20drugs%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20such%20a%20socially%20enforced%20taboo.%20Any%20kind%20of%20conversation%20about%20anything%20good%20about%20drugs%20is%20seen%20as%20encouraging%20experimentation%20%E2%80%94%20like%2C%20'Can't%20wait%20until%20you%20get%20to%20do%20some!'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20taboos%20are%20a%20major%20reason%20many%20parents%20keep%20their%20drug%20use%20confined%20to%20a%20close-knit%20group%20of%20friends.%20Joyce%2C%20a%2044-year-old%20mom%20of%20three%20in%20Melbourne%2C%20Australia%2C%20said%20it's%20not%20unusual%20in%20her%20high-income%20neighborhood%20to%20gather%20at%20someone's%20house%2C%20open%20up%20a%20nice%20bottle%20of%20wine%2C%20and%20discreetly%20visit%20the%20master%20bathroom%20for%20a%20line%20of%20communal%20cocaine.%20She%20and%20her%20neighborhood%20friends%20have%20been%20doing%20it%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20the%20same%20people%20who%20are%20taking%20vacations%20two%2C%20three%2C%20four%20times%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Joyce%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20drive%20nice%20cars.%20They%20live%20in%20beautiful%20homes.%20You%20walk%20down%20a%20street%20in%20the%20nicest%20suburbs%2C%20and%20you%20would%20never%20even%20think%20that%20the%20people%20behind%20the%20gates%20would%20be%20having%20themselves%20a%20little%20'70s%20disco%20party%20in%20the%20kitchen.%20It's%20totally%20seen%20and%20not%20heard%2C%20but%20everybody%20does%20it.%26quot%3B%20All%20the%20while%2C%20everyone's%20kids%20are%20squirreled%20away%20somewhere%20else%20in%20the%20house%2C%20preoccupied%20by%20movies%20and%20snacks%2C%20happily%20oblivious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20live-and-let-live%20attitudes%20in%20her%20immediate%20friend%20group%2C%20Joyce%20%E2%80%94%20who%20asked%20that%20we%20keep%20her%20identity%20private%20%E2%80%94%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20legal%20and%20reputational%20risks%20that%20come%20with%20using%20drugs.%20Getting%20found%20out%20might%20not%20affect%20her%20as%20severely%20as%20it%20would%20if%20she%20were%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20well-off%20white%20mom%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20but%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20trivial%2C%20either.%20The%20penalty%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcocaine-production-record-high-level-demand-also-soaring-un-says-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecocaine%20possession%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Australia%20carries%20a%20fine%20of%202%2C000%20Australian%20dollars%2C%20or%20about%20%241%2C240%2C%20and%2For%20up%20to%20two%20years%20in%20prison.%20The%20social%20ramifications%20could